<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-08-18T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-08-18T19:00:00-05:00" n="142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/8–1850: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d142fn1">Sent also to Paris as telegram
                                867.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">limited distribution</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-08-18T20:00:00-04:00">August 18,
                                    1950—8 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>929. Eyes only for Amb no distribution. This is State–Def msg. <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> only Standing Group today began
                            consideration of more adequate and centralized measures to prepare mil
                            plans under <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>. This thought has been
                            discussed only within inner <gloss target="#t_SG1">SG</gloss> circles
                            and will be subject to study during remainder Aug. Until <gloss target="#t_SG1">SG</gloss> thinking has developed further we believe
                            it is critical that no disclosure of this info be made, on the basis
                            that any recommendations will stem from short-range plans not received
                            until Sept. In event you are approached at high governmental level we
                            suggest that noncommittal reply be made to these queries, to effect that
                            you understand the <gloss target="#t_SG1">SG</gloss> is considering such
                            a matter and that we are, of course, vitally interested in developing
                            the most effective mechanism to advance <gloss target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> mil planning.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>